ensureValidIndex

private static final <T> void ensureValidIndex(ArrayList<T> list,
                                               int index)
Forcibly increases the size of a given ArrayList to enable adding a new element with a given index by adding null references for each index between the end of the ArrayList and the given index.

Type Parameters:
T - The type of the elements in the ArrayList.
Parameters:
list - The ArrayList to increase the size of
index - The index to expand the ArrayList to.

shiftRight

protected static <LE> void shiftRight(ArrayList<LE> list,
                                      int startIndex,
                                      int endIndex,
                                      int shiftValue)
Shifts all the elements of an ArrayList between a given start and end index right by a certain amount. NOTE: Doesn't work properly for shifting to the left; That should be done by iterating forwards over the given List, while this method iterates backwards.

Parameters:
list - The given ArrayList to shift the elements thereof.
startIndex - The start index.
endIndex - The end index.
shiftValue - The amount to shift each element by, such that (newIndex = oldIndex + shiftValue).
